cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on evaluating the cross-lingual effectiveness of representations from a massively multilingual neural machine translation (NMT) model on downstream tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and related tasks such as machine translation. 

The paper also involves transfer learning and evaluation of neural network models, which are common topics in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the downstream tasks evaluated in the paper include classification and sequence labeling, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
